- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a speedup technique for Dijkstra's shortest path algorithm using data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper presents a shared-memory parallel implementation. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses the trade-off between preprocessing and query times and presents an implementation that exploits cache locality for competitive preprocessing times. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses graph theory and shortest path algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the optimization of a well-known algorithm.
